          "reviewBody": "s a parent, I really feel happy with Greenwoods School! The teachers are so good – not just for teaching but they actually care for children. They guide them properly like a mentor. Even management is very nice, they listen to parents’ feedback and try to do best for kids.\n\nOne thing I really like is e-learning in all classrooms. My child enjoys studying because of that, lessons become more interesting. Also, they give good balance between studies and activities, so children are not just studying all the time but also doing other things and learning new skills.\n\nSports also is very good here! My child now loves to play and is becoming more active. He has also learned teamwork, which is very important.\n\nOverall, Greenwoods School has a very nice environment for children to grow. I am happy that we selected this school!\n\nI will surely recommend it to all parents who want overall good education for their child! 😊",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Greenwoods School - Hadapsar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Vinod Ugale"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-12-04",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "2",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Giving 2 star rating only for teachers who are actually taking efforts in the school. Else will like to give 0 rating for the management. I haven't seen such poor management till now.\n- Still following traditional way of taking admission and office clerks are slowest employees on earth. Genuinely slower than SBI officials.\n- School should digitize everything and must have some quick office staff.\n-  Still using handwritten fee receipts and everytime parents need to carry them to the school instead keep it digitized so that parents will not be troubled as they visit school by sacrificing office hours.\n- I card photos were clicked in the June and guess when I cards were given to my kids....after diwali....When I asked for reason teachers said...photo was not submitted. I was amazed by listening such cheap reason. I took my both kids to click photos for ID and in front of me, photos were taken and confirmed. Not expecting this much gap...that was very disappointing...dont know what school management is doing there..useless.\n- In winter, for my daughter, we asked for sweater and cap...first teacher said pay some 800 rs cash at counter I will give sweater and cap to student in the class but my spouse was not able to pay amount due to rush at fee counter again it is due to slow work of clerks. Then myself visited school for the same..clerk said it was already given when you have purchased uniform. I told them we havent recieved it at that time. I had to go back to home and bring the uniform fee reciept where it is written that all given but seriously we havent got the sweater and cap.\n- clerk was telling me ki you must have lost it....again it was amazing response by the staff how a sweater and cap will be lost...height of stupidity.\n- Now they are saying that the teacher who gave you uniform set we will have confirm with them but she is on leave visit after two days. we will have to check the register.\n- Again see the their smartness....if it is in the register why not to check it now and why to wait for that teacher to come.\n\nI hope management will think twice over it and will improve their system. It is private school but office staff is like government school. As a parent, I am totally disappointed..the only reason I can think to keep my kids their for next academic year is the teachers. Management is worst..super worst.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
